Details.Title: Angie Tribeca
Details.Description: A sneak peek at Season 3 of "Angie Tribeca." Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Star Wars Rebels
Details.Description: Part 2 of 2. Hera and Kanan, trapped on Atollon with the rebel base under siege, fight to keep the squadron alive, as Ezra attempts to rally help from an unexpected source. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Star Wars Rebels
Details.Description: Part 1 of 2. In final preparations for their attack on Lothal, Phoenix Squadron's plans are disrupted when Grand Admiral Thrawn discovers their location. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Review
Details.Description: Forrest swaps roles with A.J.; tries to live like Helen Keller; and visits Suzanne to review forgiveness. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Colony
Details.Description: An attack on the Green Zone is told from five different points of view. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Baskets
Details.Description: In the Season 2 finale, Christine turns to Arby's when Chip joins the Russians. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Powerless
Details.Description: Emily learns that Jackie is in need of some extra cash, so she tries to help her out. Meanwhile, Van is on a witch hunt and has his eyes set on Teddy, Ron and Wendy. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Expanse
Details.Description: Bobbie becomes a pawn in a political struggle between Earth and Mars. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Detroiters
Details.Description: Tim and Sam get fired by a furniture store client, so they try to make an ad for its competitor, who's not exactly a natural on camera. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Americans
Details.Description: Philip and Elizabeth tell Paige more about the family business, but pressing new questions arise when an operation takes a ghastly and unexpected turn. Elsewhere: a sensitive package jeopardizes Oleg's life back home. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: HUMANS
Details.Description: In the Season 2 finale, Mattie reveals the synths' agenda and seeks out Max's help; Karen makes a life-altering decision; and Mia and Hester break into the Silo. Then, Niska and Astrid prepare to return to Berlin; and Joe leaves Laura shell-shocked. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Review
Details.Description: In the Season 2 premiere, Forrest gets into a fight with a stranger; blackmails his new girlfriend; and finds sex in a public restroom. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Last Week Tonight With John Oliver
Details.Description: The U.S. federal budget and proposed cuts by the Trump administration are discussed. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: American Crime
Details.Description: Jeanette grows suspicious of her family's intentions surrounding a devastating fire that killed several of their undocumented workers. Meanwhile, Shae is urged to testify against her former pimp by Kimara; Isaac looks out for Coy as he adjusts to a harsh new life on the farm; and Luis' search for his missing son continues. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Girls
Details.Description: Desi wants to bail on a gig that was planned for a birthday party for Marnie's mom in New Jersey. Meanwhile, Hannah turns down Adam's request to screen his film, but gets important advice from her dad and his new partner, Keith; and Elijah catches the acting bug again after helping a coworker with an audition. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Last Man on Earth
Details.Description: Melissa's pre-virus past is investigated by Todd and Tandy to find clues for her current condition, while Carol's outlook on life undergoes a major makeover. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Walking Dead
Details.Description: The Saviors pay an unexpected visit to the Hilltop, catching everyone by surprise. This time, they're planning on taking more than just supplies. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Black Sails
Details.Description: A rescue plan may come between Flint and Silver; Max discovers the real price of freedom; Rackham tracks his prey; the Walrus sails into uncharted territory. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Homeland
Details.Description: Carrie catches a break; Keane makes a plan; Max goes undercover. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Making History
Details.Description: Deborah suspects that Dan may not be the clever inventor he claimed to be back in 1776, which leads to questions about their budding relationship. Meanwhile, Chris' mentor puts him under intense scrutiny as he works to achieve tenure at the university. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Missing
Details.Description: It is now 2015 and Julien's health is failing, but his determination to track down the missing girl means he has not finished with the Webster case just yet. Back in Germany, the press descend on Eckhausen for a trial when a seemingly vital piece of new evidence comes to light. Gemma is surprised by a phone call from Julien and finds a new purpose that helps break through her stupor. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Bob's Burgers
Details.Description: Linda is excited to chaperone Tina's weekend at a heroine conference, but the girl's new friend could put the getaway in jeopardy. Meanwhile, the Belcher kids left behind formulate big plans for their home-alone weekend with Dad. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Star Wars Rebels
Details.Description: Reacting to a vision of Maul, Ezra defies Hera and Kanan to travel to a remote planet in hopes of stopping the former Sith Lord from carrying out his plans. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Colony
Details.Description: Will, Katie, and Broussard search for a way out of the colony; Maddie gets some visitors in the Green Zone; and Bram looks for closure. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Baskets
Details.Description: Martha learns to haggle. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Expanse
Details.Description: Naomi tracks down signs of protomolecule; and Fred Johnson's control over OPA collapses. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Detroiters
Details.Description: A new tech company moves into Tim and Sam's building, disrupting their daily routine, but Sam tries to hide a crush on one of the outfit's female employees. Meanwhile, Lea runs into trouble editing an ad for a local mirror store. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Americans
Details.Description: Stan and Oleg wrestle with the harsh consequences of their complicated history as Philip and Elizabeth face a new mission with devastating implications for their country. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: This Is Us
Details.Description: In the first-season finale, Jack heads to Cleveland to make things right with Rebecca on the night of her first big gig with the band. Then, Randall, Kate and Kevin make big decisions about their futures. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: HUMANS
Details.Description: In the first-half of this combined episode, Mia risks falling into the wrong hands; Odi struggles to find purpose in life; and Hester and Leo stake out the Silo, but with a fatal outcome. Then, Athena discovers Milo's real plan; and Max begins a new community of synths. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Black Sails
Details.Description: Flint urges caution on an angry Silver; Max leads Rackham and Bonny up river; Billy locates a survivor; Rogers learns the truth. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Last Week Tonight With John Oliver
Details.Description: The American Health Care Act proposed by Republicans; International Women's Day; and Wikileaks' CIA document dump are discussed. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Girls
Details.Description: Hannah's mom comes for a visit, but is preoccupied with how to accept the next phase of her life. Meanwhile, Adam and Jessa start shooting their film, but clash over his creative direction; and a grieving Ray can't count on Marnie for support. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: American Crime
Details.Description: Season 3 of this anthology series begins, and is set in North Carolina, where undocumented workers toil away for little reward; a woman starts to question the methods of the family farm she married into; and a social worker tries to make a difference. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Last Man on Earth
Details.Description: Melissa is locked up for her own good, but it only frees her up to play mind games with the group, who try to find the right medicine to help her. Meanwhile, Lewis takes off for an adventure by himself. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Walking Dead
Details.Description: Keeping with the routine supply drop-off, a group of Kingdommers deliver goods to the Saviors, but things don't go as planned. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Homeland
Details.Description: Carrie and Saul present evidence to Keane; Quinn tracks a mark. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Making History
Details.EpisodeTitle: The Shot Heard Round the World
Details.Description: Dan and Deb travel back to colonial times to rescue Chris, and turn out to be instrumental in sparking the Revolutionary War. Later, Dan and Chris go undercover as British allies in an attempt to rally the colonists to revolt. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Missing
Details.Description: Julien and Jorn's investigation leads them further into the murky underbelly of Eckhausen and the secrets of its conflicting German and British communities. However, as he gets closer to the truth, Julien is dramatically let down by his own body. The Webster family drift further and further apart as Matthew gets involved with violent thugs and Sam seeks solace elsewhere. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Bob's Burgers
Details.Description: Gene discovers that the recipe for his favorite chocolate has been altered, so he contacts the company head to get things straightened out. Meanwhile, Bob gets involved in a typically Teddy less-than-perfect plan. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Star Wars Rebels
Details.Description: Chopper and AP-5 team up to infiltrate an Imperial station to steal needed codes, but an Imperial specialist turns the droids against the crew to cause chaos. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Colony
Details.Description: Will and Katie attempt to make contact with a new arrival in the bloc; and Bob has some questions for the Bowman family. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Baskets
Details.Description: Cody gets punched when someone tries to attack Logan. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Powerless
Details.Description: Emily convinces Teddy to enter an invention into the Wayne Innovation Contest against the elitist engineers of Wayne X, even though he has his doubts. Meanwhile, Van takes advantage of Ron's good nature and has him assemble a toy in hopes of preoccupying his new girlfriend's child. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Portlandia
Details.Description: In the Season 7 finale, Sandra trains a pit bull to exhibit self-control; Lisa and Bryce engage in the business of selling instant garbage; and parents give their adult son a lesson in alcohol. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Witness
Details.Description: A series spotlighting the work of photojournalists in conflict zones around the world begins in Juárez, Mexico, where Eros Hoagland documents the violence and despair associated with drug trafficking, gang violence and law-enforcement agencies. Hoagland's father, Newsweek photographer John Hoagland, was killed in El Salvador in 1984. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Man Seeking Woman
Details.Description: In the third season finale, Josh and Lucy get married. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Expanse
Details.Description: Preparations for the Earth/Mars peace conference lead to tightening tension on Erringwright. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: Detroiters
Details.Description: Sam's dad is turning 60, but he struggles to come up with a worthy speech for his birthday party, while Tim tries to get an off-duty clown to perform at the event. Copyright Rovi, Inc.

Details.Title: The Americans
Details.Description: In the Season 5 premiere, the Centre sends a new operation unlike anything before to Philip and Elizabeth, which puts more strain on their already tense marriage and family life. Copyright Rovi, Inc.
